s country on a tourist visa with his family. Their visas expired in 1985 and <PERSON> Hobbs </PERSON> has asserted his right to citizenship since. In 1986, federal rules were changed to give citizenship rights to foreign children fathered by American men outside marriage. <PERSON> Hobbs </PERSON>' family can stay here until the case is settled. A hearing was continued to July 7.
