s from the poll, conducted last September by <ORGANIZATION> Peter </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> D. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hart </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Research </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Associates </ORGANIZATION>, appear in the April 7 issue of the magazine which went on sale today. The poll is based on interviews with 816 respondents at their homes, the magazine said. The margin of error survey is plus or minus four percent for questions involving all respondents, and slightly higher for subgroups.
