Decker withdrawing bid; No pickup</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOWSON, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Black </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Decker </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> withdrew its $ 77-a-share bid for <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>. Tuesday, halting the bidding war over the plumbing giant, and allowing a $ 2.45 billion leveraged buyout spearheaded by <ORGANIZATION> Kelso </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> to go forward Under the agreement reached Tuesday, the Towson-based tool manufacturer agreed not to purchase shares of <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION> until <PERSON> Kelso </PERSON> has had an opportunity to pursue its $ 78-a-share tender offer, according to a <ORGANIZATION> Black </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Decker </PERSON> announcement. Under the agreement, <PERSON> Kelso </PERSON> will pay <ORGANIZATION> Black </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Decker </PERSON> $ 25 million for withdrawing its bid, as soon as <PERSON> Kelso </PERSON> begins purchasing stock under its tender offer or acquires at least 20 percent of <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION>'s shares in any other transaction. `` Seventy-seven -LRB- dollars -RRB- was our top price,'' said <PERSON> Barbara </PERSON> <PERSON> Lucas </PERSON>, a <ORGANIZATION> Black </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Decker </PERSON> spokeswoman. Ms. <PERSON> Lucas </PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> Black </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Decker </PERSON> had initially thought <PERSON> Ke