</ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Decker not renewing its takeover bid for American Standard. If <PERSON> Kelso </PERSON> terminates its merger agreement with <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION> or fails to purchase shares by May 2, <ORGANIZATION> Black </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Decker </PERSON> is free to pursue the acquisition of <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION>, according to <ORGANIZATION> Black </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Decker </PERSON>. Earlier Tuesday, the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> halted trading in <ORGANIZATION> Black </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Decker </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION> shares for three hours in anticipation of an announcement by <ORGANIZATION> Black </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Decker </PERSON>. <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION> Vice President <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Torrenzano </PERSON> said at the time that <ORGANIZATION> Black </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Decker </PERSON> `` initiated a call'' to the exchange and `` shared with us information concerning the American Standard bid which materially could affect the price of their stock.'' No announcement was forthcoming. Both stocks began trading again at 1:43 p.m. EST. After resumption, <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION> rose 12.5 cents to $ 77 a share while <ORGANIZATION> Black </ORGANIZA